Feedback: In a future Version i think it would be very nice to be able to create a digital mental map yourself (with the round circles and arrows). This could help to identify one‘s one node stressor that would be the most sensible to tackle (e.g. being part of a vicious cycle). Really liked the structure (educational video and then application of learned concepts).
was great! Maybe useful to mention how those events and cycles lead to disturbs such as adhd, anxiety, etc
The last exercise was challenging. Would have liked some more guidance.

The reason I disagreed with the utility of psysys was because most of the information was not new to me, so I didn't accquire any new knowledge on my own mental health or mental health in general, but I think for a lot of people it is very useful and can be new information!

I liked the mental health map concept. I don't really see therapists use this much and IMO it is really helpful to see it in a flowchart form. The scenario in video 4 with the baby seems a bit unrealistic. Who is watching the baby when you go running? I liked the exercises.It was easy to get the hang of them, though many of the options available weren't applicable to me. Still, overall it has a lot of potential for helping people understand their cycles of distress.

Education.level: Primary education ─ primary school until middle school (~ 6 - 11 years)

Feedback: Importante que os vídeos tenham acessibilidade como Língua de sinais, legenda e audiodescrição para que pessoas com deficiência e outras possam acompanhá-lo.

The presentation along with the music was very pleasant. The constant summarization and repetition was perfect. In one of the diagrams in my opinion a node for 'intrusive thoughts' was missing between 'shame' and 'no focus' or should be at least mentioned. Some concepts like arising comorbidities should be mentioned as contributing new emerging factors. A vital point would also be that many use mental distress as excuse for things not going according to plan and start self identifying with it and feel powerless to do anything against it because that bears the risk of being more of a failure and having the excuse is easy and often is only self diagnosed which is highly advised against because of lack of differential diagnosis.
Loved that even though it was "matter of fact", it also a warm. Loved the animation. Easy to follow, easy to aply. The voice was soft and the tempo good.

very nice video, easy to understand - Emily has a very nice calm voice, my problem: I dont think it is that "easy" to deal with your stress by only realizing what you need to change - e.g. I want to go to the psychologist but somehow cant because I want to get "verbeamtet" - so I feel like I cant do anything about my stress, because I know it is linked to my childhood - but I cant help myself so still have the feeling I cant change anything, it will not end (even if its not about the fact that you wanted me to lo learn to understand that I can change my mental health - somehow I cant, thats why I had to answer like I did) - now you get answers which are probably not what you wanted to hear - but somehow you asked for it - so maybe the questions were not that clear
I would have liked more support on how I can figure out these things for my own mental health.

I like the general idea of mindmapping ones problems to visualise links and triggers. I found the videos a bit too slow, so I set the setting to 1.25 speed, I feel like this might be different for people with other English speaking skills or educational backround though.
I would like to have access to the resources (videos) afetr the study as well as they would help me to draw my own mental health map.
I liked the fact how you made such a concept so very understandable/graspable, in such a short time. thanks!

Good tool. But just for those who reflect that they need it. Over- oder underconfident or tunneled people will not use it.  Advice in the video is too easy (in my eyes), as there are restrictive and very influencing factors and interactions not easy changeable - vicious cyces are hard to overcome, but this tool may help to get contact to professionals. Additional the map is static, but most we do and experience is dynamic.
